            <h5 class="card-title">OOP Task Management System</h5>

            <p class="card-text">
             Developed a Python console application simulating a real-world study planner for students.<br>
              It leverages object-oriented programming (OOP) principles including encapsulation, class design and object collaboration across multiple entities <br>
              It also represents my initiative to learn beyond my academic syllabus to develop this project and learn more advanced OOP concepts.<br>
             
            </p>

           

            <strong>Key Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Add subjects and tasks with deadlines.</li>
                <li>Mark tasks complete, detect overdue work.</li>
                <li>Schedule,update, and cancel study sessions</li>
                <li>Generate reminders and prioritize tasks.</li>
                <li> Produce simple schedules for all tasks.</li>
            </ul>
         
          
           <p class="card-text">
              <strong>Tech Stack: </strong><br>
              Language: Python 3.x <br>
              Paradigm: Object-Oriented Programming<br>
